for applying validation:-
1.@NonNull :- filed not null rehvi joiee but eni under empty value chale example:-empty string or an empty collection
2.@NotEmpty:- this emsure that field is non null and also not empty example:- at least one character
3.@NotBlank:- this is only apply on string and ensure they are not null , not empty and contrain at least one non-whitespace character


##note NotEmpty cannot be use in int double or anything
make sure it is use in only String

and entity per lagadiee validatio tyare NotBlank use nai karvanu baki error avse
NotBlank only for the string

for entity use NotNull



Field Type	Correct Annotation
String	@NotBlank
List	@NotEmpty
boolean	@NotNull (use Boolean, not boolean)
double	@Positive, @Min, @DecimalMin
Entity reference	@NotNull

note:- string mi size ma validation mate @Min ke @Max use nai thayy e int long and double e badha mate che
      for string use @Size(max = 50, message = "Name length must not exceed 50")

and use this dependency:-
	<dependency>
			<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
			<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-validation</artifactId>
	</dependency>

